  "prompt": "If I don't clear the ASAT, will I not be able to get into the ALLEN Career Institute?",
  "response": "The ASAT (ALLEN Scholarship Admission Test) is an entrance test conducted by ALLEN Career Institute to assess students for admission and scholarships. While performance in the ASAT can impact your eligibility for scholarships and may be a requirement for certain programs, it's important to check directly with ALLEN Career Institute regarding their specific admission criteria.\n\nIn some cases, there may be alternative admission processes or criteria that do not necessarily require clearing the ASAT, such as direct admissions based on previous academic performance or other factors. To get accurate and detailed information, it would be best to contact ALLEN Career Institute directly or visit their official website.",
